  <section xml:id="sec-getting-selinux">
    <title>Getting SELinux</title>
    <para>
      SELinux is installed by default when installing by &yast; or is part of the raw images. By default the SELinux state is <literal>disabled</literal>. To set the SELinux mode to <literal>enforcing</literal> and configure your system properly for using SELinux, run the following command: 
    </para>
    <screen>&prompt.root;transactional-update setup-selinux</screen>
    <para>
The command installs the SELinux policy if it is not installed, sets the SELinux mode to <literal>enforcing</literal> and rebuilts <literal>initrd</literal>.
    </para>
  </section>

